str2: Answer, bid, bring word, command. A primary verb; to speak or say.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: (a) I cast, throw, rush, (b) often, in the weaker sense: I place, put, drop. A primary verb; to throw.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A fishing-net. Probably from a primary verb diko; a seine.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
On the right hand, right hand, right. From dechomai; the right side or hand.

The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A ship, vessel, boat. From pleo; a sailer, i.e. Vessel.

str2: A prolonged form of a primary heuro, which heureo is used for it in all the tenses except the present and imperfect to find.

str2: To have strength, be strong, be in full health and vigor, be able; meton: I prevail. From ischus; to have force.
